BTW - I recently download PMD, and it showed me some interesting 
things in our current project.  I thought it'd be equally as 
interesting to run it against the JUnit source (since I'm messing 
with the source anyway).

Most of the things it found were lack of curly braces and empty catch 
blocks, but there were a few other tidbits like:

swingui.TestRunner   -unused formal parameter 'kind'         -line 125
swingui.TestRunner   -unused private fields 'PLAIN_FONT'     -line 24
swingui.TestRunner   -unused private fields 'BOLD_FONT'      -line 25
runner.TextRunnerTest-duplicate import 'java.io.IOException' -line 7
runner.TextRunnerTest-duplicate import 'junit.framework.TestResult'- 
line 4
swingui.CounterPanel -unused private method 'asString'       -line 107
framework.Assert     -unused formal parameter 'expected'     -line 267
awtui.TestRunner     -unused private field 'SUITE_METHODNAME'-line 43


-Eric
